<h1 id="recap">Recap</h1>
<p><code>let</code> is the new <code>var</code>. <code>const</code> is the same, but doesn't let you change it.</p>
<pre><code class="language-js">let a = 'hello'
const b = 'hi'
</code></pre>
<p>They are &quot;block scoping&quot;: they are only available within <code>{...}</code> blocks, but not outside them.</p>
<pre><code class="language-js">if (true) {
  let a = 'hello'
}
console.log(a)  //=&gt; undefined
</code></pre>
<ul>
<li></li>
</ul>
